BA UBS reiterates Boeing Buy rating sees 737 MAX stigma fading Boeing BA 16 rebounds a bit as UBS reiterates its Buy rating and 500 price target for the stock saying it expects the stigma over the grounded 737 MAX to fade among consumers with no significant share erosion According to a UBS survey of more than 1000 US residents about their views of the MAX debacle 70 of respondents said they would have some hesitation about booking a flight on a MAX but nearly twothirds said they never or seldom checked the kind of plane on which they fly and only 12 of respondents who have some hesitation suggested that their concerns could not be addressed with continued safe operation of the plane The net result is the survey suggests 8 of the flying public would never fly the 737 MAX but when coupled with booking habits also captured in the survey the percentage drops to about 3 UBS says
